cumulated.pretty:
⊢ (w0 →(HomF ` c0)=(HomF ` c1))
⊣ (w0 →(Homf ` c0)=(Homf ` c1))
⊣ (w0 → c0 ∈ Cat)
⊣ (w0 →(comf ` c0)=(comf ` c1))
⊣ (w0 → c1 ∈ Cat)

comment: If two categories have the same set of objects, morphisms, and compositions, then they have the same Hom functor. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 26-Jan-2017.)
